div.p:
The research on identifying and measuring bias in datasets is rapidly advancing (Ferrara 2023) alongside the growth of artificial intelligence applications (Schwartz et al. 2022). Frameworks are proposed for humanistic datasets (Rane 2023), including those focusing on textual and hate speech biases (Raza 2024). This study references the first two levels of the Wich’s framework (Meta and Semantic) (Wich et al. 2022). Levels 3 and 4 address biases in applied research and are considered for future exploration. Additionally, the results are illustrated with specific visualizations using Python libraries (MatplotLib 
                    , Seaborn 
                    ) and the Variationist tool (Ramponi et al. 2024), which effectively explores and visualizes variation and bias in textual data.
